In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses a variety of topics. He mentions that the President called King Abdullah of Saudi Arabia and King Hamad of Bahrain to discuss the situation in Bahrain. He also talks about the deteriorating situation at the nuclear power plant in Japan and the recommendation from the Nuclear Regulatory Commission (NRC) for American citizens within a 50-mile radius of the plant to evacuate. Carney emphasizes that the advice from the NRC is based on their independent analysis of the situation and the standards set by the NRC in the United States. He also addresses questions about the missing journalists in Libya and the release of Raymond Davis in Pakistan. Carney defends the administration's commitment to transparency and openness and mentions that the President will receive a transparency award from an outside organization. He also discusses the ongoing budget negotiations and the situation in Afghanistan.